This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it proposes a protocol for trading ML models that is focused on security and privacy. The paper also discusses possible improvements to the protocol to make it more efficient and secure, which further supports its classification under cs.CR. The paper also touches upon topics related to machine learning (ML) and distributed computing (DC), which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses software engineering (SE) aspects of the protocol, such as implementation and testing, which makes cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses potential cyber threats and attacks, which makes cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible sub-category as well.
